  "text": "Patient 8 developed septic shock with blood cultures positive for Staphylococcus haemolyticus and acute kidney injury with a peak creatinine of 542 mmol/l, and this coincided with a marked rise in levels of NGAL and lysozyme (Figure 2b ). This most likely reflected non-myeloid expression, as NGAL is an established marker of acute kidney injury, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and lysozyme is induced in a number of tissues in response to inflammation. [CITATION_3] Also note that proHNPs and MPO remained stable during the systemic infection, their eventual rise reflecting myelopoiesis.",
